.I exception Failure 

.sp
Raised by parsers when none of the first components of the stream
patterns is accepted\&.

.sp

.I exception Error 
.B of 
.B string

.sp
Raised by parsers when the first component of a stream pattern is
accepted, but one of the following components is rejected\&.

.sp

.I val from 
: 
.B (int -> 'a option) -> 'a t
.sp

.B Stream\&.from f
returns a stream built from the function 
.B f
\&.
To create a new stream element, the function 
.B f
is called with
the current stream count\&. The user function 
.B f
must return either
.B Some <value>
for a value or 
.B None
to specify the end of the
stream\&.
.sp
Do note that the indices passed to 
.B f
may not start at 
.B 0
in the
general case\&. For example, 
.B [< \&'0; \&'1; Stream\&.from f >]
would call
.B f
the first time with count 
.B 2
\&.

.sp

